beer_description:
Light-bodied pale, with a moderate bitterness, 
provides a cool refreshing finish.

Orchard Gate Gold is fermented naturally in small artisanal batches from a proprietary blend of organic apples grown here at our Koan Family Orchards in Michigan. We have produced hard ciders here since the 1860s. This is the same traditional recipe that helped save our farm during the great depression. There will be slight variations from batch to batch, just as nature makes no two apples alike! Enjoy our authentic hand bottled American Farmhouse "Scrumpy" Cider with family, friends & food.

beer_description: Unique mild beer with a velvety taste. You cannot drink fast, but on the contrary you want to savor sip by sip. Manufactured by proprietary recipe. Is unique in the market.

Nile Special has been the flagship brand of Nile 
Breweries for the past 50 years. Over the 
generations, it has been trusted for its consistency.
An eight times Gold Awardwinning beer at the 
Brussels-based Monde Selection International.
Brewed longer for easy drinking, slower for great taste.

A premium lager beer brewed from the finest ingredients, Singha is a full-bodied 100% barley malt beer that is distinctively rich in taste with strong hop characters. Brewed with three hops: Saaz, Perle and Hallertau. 

Editor?s Note: Recipe scaled down from 6% to 5% in 2007.
Cheers X-Tra is an European-inspired high alcohol beer. Cheers X-Tra?s strength lies its use of only the finest imported ingredients, giving Cheers X-Tra it?s unmistaken crisp refreshing taste.

A crisp champagne-like beer with fine bubbles and a fruity, spicy aroma. The crisp clean malt character and delicate fruit notes in this beer are complemented by a slight citrus flavor from dry hopping with Bavarian Noble hops. Bottle conditioning adds another layer of complexity and light spice notes.
Contents from fine quality malt and hop, with natural water, and selected yeast, especially for Beer Chang. Brewed at Cosmos Brewery (Thailand) Co., Ltd.

ThaiBev stopped production of Chang Beer, Chang Draught, and Chang Export in 2015. 

A new product, Chang Classic, was launched, with production shared between ThaiBev?s three breweries.

Ingredients: Fine quality malt, rice, and hop, with natural water, and selected yeast.
"With its attractive taste and a price that appealed to consumers at all levels, the response and success of Chang marked a new era and turned a new page for the Thai beer industry. In 1998 Beer Chang was awarded the ?Gold Medallion? at the International Beer Competition in Australia in the category of ?Lager, Unlimited Degree?.
Cheers? unique aromatic scent and taste will delight drinkers who appreciate an international standard of beer.

Born of the fortuitous encounter between a string stout and fermented apricots from the Valais which never reached the distillers, our Oud Bruin (Flemish for ?old brown?) is a rather unorthodox take on the style. It nevertheless boasts the typical sweet and sour balance between a solid malty, toffee-like, chocolaty, roasted and fruity backbone, into which the apricot wine merges seamlessly with its lactic sourness, its leathery, horse blanket notes from wild yeasts and a discrete touch of apricot deep down. It finally evolves harmoniously into a slightly bitter finish. Altogether a pretty unique yet very drinkable beer, between sweetness, fruitiness and sourness, going down well with lamb and duck meat, mussels, shellfish and hard cheeses.

Contains carbohydrates, unmalted cereals, antioxidant. Pale color, white head quickly quite persistent, unmalted stuff smell. Aroma grains, unmalted stuff. Dusty sweetish taste, ultra carbonated. Cheap and weak, much better than the "sub zero".

My beer "season" were developed during my stay in Canada. The recipe was inspired by a book (Farmhouse Ales - Phil Markowski). The beers were traditionally brewed in season winter farm-breweries of Wallonia. Brewers made ??up the recipe with ingredients from the last harvest and proceeded to re-fermentation in the bottle which often lasted until harvest following. Summer workers (seasonal) received this beer to drink. My interpretation is rather attenuated (little / no residual sugar) with an alcohol content (6% +) to allow for long aging. This beer can be kept 12-18 months before consumption. Notes of yeast are present, due to high fermentation. For those who do not know, this golden lager, is very elegant and very fruity. This is my version of a bear with a reinforced hopping: 50 IBU for "only" 5.2 to 5.5% alcohol. It contains virtually the content of hops IPA, but its black-brown stems of roasted malts. I stirred once or twice per year.

It is a mixed fermentation beer contains Pale and Pure Lambic. Aged in oak barrels for 12 months and 12 months in bottle, so beer is a seasonal produce only once a year, hence has the name of September. We love this beer for before meals, and drink it with strong cheeses, olives and seafood or fruits of the sea.
Recommended jug used in this way, good oxygenation of beer.
Low alcohol session beer with intense aroma and flavour. Amarillo single hop.

Carob colored with red highlights and fine bubbles. The modest head is cream in color. A symphony of toasted and cereal aromas fill the nose, evoking the crust of country bread, cocoa, hazelnut and chestnut. There is a vague trace of red fruit. Also hints of cinammon and organic flavors. The first taste comes on sweet, light and gentle with a marked acidity in contrast to the toasted flavors. The mouthfeel is both creamy and light.

The lingering aromas stand out boldly ? smoke and brine (sea salt) recall the peaty moors of Scotland.

Cervesa Artesanal de Tarragon. This honey colored ale is elegant with a certain density in the glass, foam creamy white ivory tones and consistent with good persistence. Due to the presence of yeast in the second fermentation, the appearance is cloudy.

Montejo represents the experience and attributes of the country where it was born: adherence to tradition and culture, pride derived from accomplishments and hard work, and aspirations to achieve greatness.

Montejo has a light golden color and is renowned for its crisp, refreshing finish. Although a lighter lager, Montejo is smooth and full-flavored.

Cerveza Pac?fico Clara, better known as Pacifico, is a Mexican pilsner-style beer. It was first brewed in 1900 when three Germans opened a brewery, the Cerveceria del Pac?fico in Mazatl?n. Cerveza Pacifico is named so because the Pacifico brewery is located in the Pacific Ocean port city of Mazatl?n, in the state of Sinaloa, M?xico. Its label includes a picture depicting a lifesaver encompassing a hill with the port's lighthouse, known locally as "Cerro del Crest?n." In Mazatl?n, the beer is available in three different size bottles: "cuartitos" (6 fl. oz), "medias" (12 fl. oz.), and "ballenas" (32 fl. oz.). "Clara" means clear, as opposed to "obscura" (dark).

beer_description: My homebrewed holiday ale with spices

One of the earliest examples of the Russian Imperial Stout in the United States, Expedition Stout offers immensely complex flavors crafted specifically with vintage aging in mind, as its profile will continue to mature and develop over the years. A huge malt body is matched to a heady blend of chocolate, dark fruits, and other aromas. Intensely bitter in its early months, the flavors will slowly meld and grow in depth as the beer ages.
